This is the process I followed to install wireshark on Ubuntu
#Links that helped
https://www.maketecheasier.com/using-wireshark-ubuntu/
http://askubuntu.com/questions/74059/how-do-i-run-wireshark-with-root-privileges

sudo apt-get install wireshark
sudo dpkg-reconfigure wireshark-common
sudo adduser cloudcowboy wireshark
sudo which dumpcap
sudo chmod 4711 /usr/bin/dumpcap  
sudo chmod 4711 /usr/bin/dumpcap